  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Supervisor",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Supervise and coordinate daily construction activities, with a strong focus on tunnel works.</p></li><li><p>Ensure all works are carried out according to approved drawings, specifications, method statements, and safety requirements.</p></li><li><p>Manage site workers, subcontractors, and equipment to meet project schedules and quality standards.</p></li><li><p>Monitor site progress and report daily activities to the Project Manager / Site Engineer.</p></li><li><p>Conduct toolbox meetings and enforce workplace safety, health, and environmental regulations.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with engineers and relevant parties to resolve site issues promptly.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper housekeeping and compliance with authority requirements.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>3–5 years of relevant experience</strong> in construction supervision.</p></li><li><p><strong>Must have tunnel construction experience</strong> (e.g. bored tunnel, cut-and-cover, underground works).</p></li><li><p>Familiar with construction safety regulations and site procedures.</p></li><li><p>Ability to supervise workers and coordinate with subcontractors effectively.</p></li><li><p>Willing and able to work <strong>night shifts</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Good communication and leadership skills.</p></li><li><p>Relevant construction or safety certifications will be an advantage.</p></li></ul>",
